\ to-slice! ( v0 v1 ... vN-1 target offset N -- target )
\ Writes N stack values into target[offset..offset+N-1] in source order.
\ Top value (vN-1) goes to target[offset+N-1]. Leaves target on stack.

99 88 77 [ 0 0 0 ] 0 3 to-slice! . cr        \ [ 99 88 77 ]
99 88 77 [ 0 0 0 0 0 ] 1 3 to-slice! . cr    \ [ 0 99 88 77 0 ]
1 2 3 4 5 [ 0 0 0 0 0 ] 0 5 to-slice! . cr   \ [ 1 2 3 4 5 ]

\ count=0 is a no-op
"keep" [ 1 2 3 ] 1 0 to-slice! . cr          \ [ 1 2 3 ]
.s clear cr                                  \ [ keep ]

\ Mixed value types
"hi" :sym 42 [ 0 0 0 ] 0 3 to-slice! . cr    \ [ hi :sym 42 ]

\ Errors
[ 0 0 0 ] 5 3 to-slice!
[ 0 0 0 ] 0 -1 to-slice!
99 88 77 42 0 3 to-slice!
1 2 [ 0 0 0 0 0 ] 0 5 to-slice!
